Description: TMJOs GNOME Shell tweaks (hide Activities button)
 Hides the GNOME Activities button in the top-left corner of the
 panel — TMJOs uses Plank's "Todos os Apps" launcher as the entry
 point to the apps overview, so the Activities button is redundant
 and visually clutters the top bar.
 .
 Implementation:
  - Uses dpkg-divert to take ownership of /usr/share/gnome-shell/
    theme/Yaru/gnome-shell.css and Yaru-dark variant. The original
    files are renamed with .tmjos-orig suffix so removing this
    package restores them cleanly.
  - Appends a small CSS rule to the diverted files that sets
    visibility:hidden + width:0 on the activities button.
 .
 Reversible: removing the package undoes the divert and restores
 the upstream Yaru theme bytes for byte.

